title: Dziupla
typeOfFood: Vegan-friendly, Lacto, Ovo, Take-out, Catering, European, Fusion, Polish
description: Hidden in a backyard, enter from Puławskiego street. Its design refers to forest, nest, hollow of tree. Serves vegetarian and vegan dishes for breakfast, dinner, appetizer, and dessert including: bruschetta with tomatoes, chia pudding and tofurnik (cheesecake with tofu), tomato or pumpkin soup, and as main dish for example falafel from chickpeas served with vegetables couscous and salad.
